  "excerpt": "<p>Get started managing and analyzing your metadata with DataTools Pro</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-1 one-column\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">Log in with Salesforce.com</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">DataTools Pro is a <a href=\"https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=sf.connected_app_overview.htm&amp;language=en_US&amp;type=5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Salesforce connected app\">Salesforce.com connected app</a>. designed to enhance common tasks related to understanding metadata relationships like entity relationships, data dictionary, metrics, and analytics. To set up DataTools Pro, as of Oct 2025, you need a Salesforce administrator. <a href=\"/tutorials/salesforce-admin-install-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Admin install guide\">View DataTools Pro Salesforce Admin guide</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Troubleshooting Login Issues</strong><br>Salesforce <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/salesforce-oauth_approval_error_generic/\" title=\"OAUTH_APPROVAL_ERROR_GENERIC\">OAUTH_APPROVAL_ERROR_GENERIC</a> &#8211; Solved</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><strong>What data does DataTools Pro access from Salesforce.com?<br></strong>Data Tools Pro is designed to connect only to Salesforce object metadata (object names, fields) and record metadata for Reports and Dashboards (report names, folders, last updated date). Data Tools Pro does not access or query any of your object record data that would contain customer information.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/datatoolspro-data-security-faq/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Security FAQ\">Security FAQ</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/security-policy-salesforce-connected-app/\" title=\"DataTools Security Policy\">DataTools Pro Security Policy</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/authorizing-an-salesforce-uninstalled-app/\" title=\"Authorizing Salesforce to DataTools\">2025 Changes: Authorizing DataTools Connected App</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">Connect to your Salesforce Objects</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><strong>Object Explorer: </strong>By default, you land on the <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/object-explorer-for-datatools-pro-dictionary/\" title=\"Object Explorer for DataTools Pro Dictionary\">Object Dictionary</a>. The first step is to connect to the Salesforce objects that you want to understand, document, visualize, and/or migrate.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Click &#8220;Select Objects&#8221;.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"98\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-8-1024x98.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9274\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-8-1024x98.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-8-300x29.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-8-768x74.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-8-1536x147.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-8-2048x196.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Choose the Salesforce objects that you actively manage for your job role.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. You can organize and categorize your Salesforce objects according to any business function, module or app using our <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-tools-erd-and-object-views/\" title=\"Data Tools Object and ERD Views\">object views feature</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><strong>Field Dictionary</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">1. Click on any object name </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"682\" height=\"544\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-9.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9276\" style=\"width:245px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-9.png 682w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-9-300x239.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 682px) 100vw, 682px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">2. The <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/salesforce-field-dictionary-with-datatools-pro/\" title=\"Salesforce Field Dictionary with DataTools Pro\">field dictionary</a> will display a list of all fields along with pertinent data from Salesforce. This information can be refreshed on demand, or for Salesforce admins you can navigate directly to the object inside of Salesforce to perform admin tasks:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"277\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-10-1024x277.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9277\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-10-1024x277.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-10-300x81.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-10-768x208.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-10-1536x416.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-10-2048x555.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From the field dictionary, you have several features for viewing field changes, navigate to the Salesforce object manager (if you have the Salesforce permissions). View the <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/salesforce-field-dictionary-with-datatools-pro/\" title=\"Salesforce Field Dictionary with DataTools Pro\">Field Dictionary</a> documentation for a complete list of features</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">Visualize your Objects in an Entity Relationship Diagram</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">1. Select the <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/salesforce-erd-step-by-step-guide/\" title=\"Salesforce Entity Relationship Diagram Step by Step Guide\">Entity Diagram</a> button option on the top navigation bar to view an interactive representation of the objects you have chosen. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">You can always return to the dictionary tab to add more objects.  As you accumulate objects, your ERD can get very crowded. For context we provide <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-tools-erd-and-object-views/\" title=\"Data Tools Object and ERD Views\">object views feature</a> for your ERD. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"How to Create Salesforce Entity Relationship Diagram\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/lHfOyQRie3w?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Manage your Salesforce Related Metrics and KPIs</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Our roots as an &#8220;analytics first&#8221; team drove us to help organizations simplify curating and preparing a smart metrics glossary. We invite you to our new <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/getting-started-with-metrics-glossary-datatools-for-salesforce/\" title=\"Getting started guide\">Metrics Dictionary Getting Started Guide!</a></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Manage and Map your Fields for Salesforce Data Migration</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If found DataTools Pro in search for a solution to help you with Salesforce data migrations we have a <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/salesforce-migration-services/salesforce-data-migration/\" title=\"Mastering Salesforce Data Migration in 2024: Tips and Tools for a Successful Launch\">migration guide</a> and brand <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/migrate-data-into-salesforce-video-series/\" title=\"Migrate Data into Salesforce Video Series\">new migration video series</a> where we show you how we completed our own migration into Salesforce</p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">Visit our DataTools Pro Support Hub</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/support/\" title=\"Support – DataTools Pro\">Visit DataTools Pro Support Hub</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/newsletters/datatools-pro-monthly-flash-7139795009523916800/?utm_source=linkedin&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=erdstorytelling&amp;utm_campaign=blogpost?utm_source=linkedin&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=erdstorytelling&amp;utm_campaign=blogpost#gf_5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&nbsp;Join our monthly newsletter&nbsp;</a><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/newsletters/datatools-pro-monthly-flash-7139795009523916800/?utm_source=linkedin&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=erdstorytelling&amp;utm_campaign=blogpost?utm_source=linkedin&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=erdstorytelling&amp;utm_campaign=blogpost#gf_5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">on&nbsp;</a><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/newsletters/datatools-pro-monthly-flash-7139795009523916800/?utm_source=linkedin&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=erdstorytelling&amp;utm_campaign=blogpost?utm_source=linkedin&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=erdstorytelling&amp;utm_campaign=blogpost#gf_5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">LinkedIn</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/datatoolspro/?utm_source=linkedin&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=erdstorytelling&amp;utm_campaign=blogpost\"> Follow us on Reddit</a></p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n"
